#!/usr/bin/env -S perl -CS

use v5.40;
use FindBin '$Bin';
use lib "$Bin/../lib";
use App::GitSummarise;

App::GitSummarise->new->run;

__END__

=head1 NAME

git-month-summary - Summarise a month of Git activity using an LLM

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  git-month-summary --month N --year YYYY [options]

  git-month-summary --month 3 --year 2026
  git-month-summary --month 3 --year 2026 --dir /home/user/repos
  git-month-summary --month 3 --year 2026 --model gpt-5.4

=head1 DESCRIPTION

C<git-month-summary> scans a directory tree for Git repositories,
collects the commit log for a specified month, and sends it to the
OpenAI Chat Completions API to produce a concise Markdown summary of
each repository's activity during that month.

Output is written to standard output in Markdown format, with each
repository under its own C<##> heading followed by 2-5 bullet points
describing the changes made during that month.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<--month> I<N>

Month number, 1 to 12.  Required.

=item B<--year> I<YYYY>

Four-digit year.  Required.

=item B<--dir> I<PATH>

Root directory to search for Git repositories.
Defaults to F<~/git>.

=item B<--model> I<MODEL>

OpenAI model name to use for summarisation.
Defaults to C<gpt-5.4-mini>.

=item B<--max-input-len> I<N>

Maximum number of characters of C<git log> output to send to the
model per repository.  Defaults to C<30000>.

=back

=head1 ENVIRONMENT

=over 4

=item C<OPENAI_API_KEY>

Must be set to a valid OpenAI API key.  The script dies immediately
if this variable is not set.

=back

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<App::GitSummarise>

